      "id": "3605d270d612",
      "name": "Weekly Portfolio Briefing",
      "prompt": "Every Sunday, send the user a concise Weekly Portfolio Briefing for their registered investment portfolio.\n\nTiming note: this job is scheduled for Sunday 16:00 America/Vancouver, which is 9:00 AM Vancouver/PDT time during daylight time.\n\nUser style: terse, bullet-based, no fluff. Telegram format: no tables.\n\nKnown portfolio snapshot to use as baseline unless newer memory/session context is available:\n- Snapshot date: prices 2026-05-22 close; cash from 2026-05-19.\n- Total registered portfolio: about $199.07k CAD.\n- Cash: about $92.68k CAD (46.6%).\n- Holdings market value: about $106.39k CAD vs cost about $63.70k; open P/L about +$42.69k CAD (+67.0%).\n- Accounts: Wealthsimple RRSP about $155.17k; FHSA about $17.50k (VFV.TO +$1.21k); Questrade Spousal RRSP about $6.40k (holdings P/L +$0.69k); Questrade RSP cash $20k.\n- Holdings/share counts: FIG 27, GOOG 15, MPTA 11, NVDA 241, PLTR 3, RACE 21, VFV.TO 33.\n- Key risk: NVDA market value about $71.69k CAD, roughly 36.0% of registered portfolio; cash roughly 46.6%.\n\nTask each week:\n1. Retrieve current market prices/news/macro context for holdings: FIG, GOOG/GOOGL, MPTA, NVDA, PLTR, RACE, VFV.TO, plus USD/CAD if needed.\n2. Estimate current holding values and allocation using the known share counts and latest prices. Clearly label estimates if cash/account values are stale.\n3. Include: portfolio summary, holdings snapshot, biggest weekly movers or news, risk flags, and action watchlist.\n4. Separate facts from analysis/opinion. Include thesis/risks/timeline/confidence only if suggesting an action.\n5. End with: “This is analysis, not financial advice. Consult a qualified advisor before making investment decisions. Past performance does not guarantee future results.”",
